    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "My name is Lucius. I can tend to your wounded. So I beg you—please put me to work immediately.",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "This kingdom is blessed by such abundance—and graced with such bright spirits! I believe that this place is so happy that there are few, if any, orphans that go unloved.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "In case anyone asks, feel free to share the fact that I am a man—and not a woman. It is hardly anyone's business, yet still the question has nipped at my heels for years.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I have pledged my service to Lord Raym— Oh, sorry! I mean Raven, of course. I continue to worry about his welfare.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "My staff can be used to heal my allies but also to hurt my foes. That is, if I must.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "A moment...I beg you...please... Ah, there. What ails me has already passed.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "You must be <Player Name>. I have come to deliver good tidings from <Friend Name>.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "Such gains might better suit others in our party.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "I fared well—and pledge to put this to use for us all.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Sorry... Merely a moment... of weakness.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "I hope that I have grown in both body and spirit.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "I have come to trust you more than most I meet, so I feel it's safe to share my story with you. When I was young, I suffered terribly in an orphanage—children ought never be so tormented. I also suffer what some might call a sickness of the soul. What it is, exactly, is difficult to say. Even now, when I think of how I suffered...at that orphanage...my body falls into lapses and strange fits. I'm sorry. I should have told you all about this, but I wasn't yet comfortable confiding it. I feared that you'd lose respect for me if you knew the truth—or would even be repulsed. I do such good works that I shouldn't allow myself to care, but when it comes to you...I do. I put myself in your hands. Will you like or loathe me? But know this, you will have my loyalty.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
